    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nThe 'confirm' prompt is not useful / misleading when working with unnamed buffers and `nohidden`. In these circumstances, it asks whether to save the buffer, but then does nothing. This behaviour is confusing and not helpful. `confirm` should either not prompt in these cases or (preferred) it should prompt for the name of a file to save to, and then carry out the original action.\r\n\r\nThis bug is also present in Vim, so if you'd prefer I open it there first, I can.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n* `nvim --clean`\r\n* `:set nohidden`\r\n* `:set confirm`\r\n* Enter insert mode and enter anything into the scratch/unnnamed buffer\r\n* `:e ~/any/existing/file.txt<CR>`\r\n* At the confirm prompt, hit 'y'\r\n* (This is the bug) Nothing happens - no switch to new buffer, no prompt for name of file.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeoVim prompts for the name of the file to be saved, saves it, then switches to the new buffer.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.0-dev-622+g08ebf8d3a\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nYes, VIM - Vi IMproved 9.0 (2022 Jun 28, compiled Dec 11 2022 13:50:40) Included patches: 1-1046\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.26.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nnvenv",
